01:46.206 --> 01:47.606
Look, I told you
I'm coming, okay?

01:47.608 --> 01:49.374
Is she still
at the apartment?

01:49.376 --> 01:52.244
Okay, just keep her there
until I can get her, okay?

01:52.246 --> 01:54.213
Hold on a second.

02:04.457 --> 02:06.258
Look what she did to me.

02:06.260 --> 02:07.759
She slammed the door
in my hand.

02:07.761 --> 02:09.862
I'm sorry.
I'm gonna deal with it, okay?

02:09.864 --> 02:13.398
Cami? Cami, it's Autumn.
Open the door.

02:16.536 --> 02:17.803
Just stay here.

02:17.805 --> 02:20.439
I'm not going in there.

02:26.713 --> 02:28.747
Cami?

02:43.329 --> 02:45.397
Cami, where are you?

02:58.912 --> 03:02.281
Sis, so glad
you could make it.

03:02.283 --> 03:03.549
Cami, what are you doing?

03:03.551 --> 03:06.919
Are you off
your medication?

03:06.921 --> 03:08.820
You mean
the mind-controlling pills?

03:08.822 --> 03:10.355
I'm not thinking
their thoughts anymore.

03:10.357 --> 03:11.857
Those pills
are implanted with memories.

03:11.859 --> 03:13.625
You're just trying
to make me the same as them!

03:13.627 --> 03:15.460
Let's just relax, okay?
Let's just sit down, okay?

03:15.462 --> 03:17.396
Look, what happened
to all your furniture?

03:19.366 --> 03:21.500
Cami, listen to me, okay?

03:21.502 --> 03:24.636
Let's just talk, okay?
Just talk to me, okay?

03:24.638 --> 03:27.206
I found it, sis.

03:27.208 --> 03:29.341
Found what?

03:29.343 --> 03:30.943
The chip.

03:30.945 --> 03:33.979
What are you talking about?

03:33.981 --> 03:37.583
The g.P.S. Chip.
It's in my finger.

03:37.585 --> 03:39.218
They didn't think
I'd find it.

03:39.220 --> 03:41.520
Okay, okay,
let's just sit down--

03:41.522 --> 03:43.589
and they've been visiting me
and leaving clues at my door,

03:43.591 --> 03:44.957
and they're just
trying to trick me.

03:44.959 --> 03:46.592
Get her crazy ass
out of here right now!

03:46.594 --> 03:48.260
And he's one of them!

03:48.262 --> 03:49.528
He is not a manager!

03:49.530 --> 03:51.296
He is a plant working
for the CIA,

03:51.298 --> 03:52.831
and they know
that I know about them.

03:52.833 --> 03:54.466
They know that I know
about the mission to Mars,

03:54.468 --> 03:55.734
aliens, NSA.

03:55.736 --> 03:57.636
I gotta-- I gotta--

03:57.638 --> 03:59.504
I gotta expose them.
I gotta expose them.

03:59.506 --> 04:02.307
It might just save you all.

04:02.309 --> 04:06.878
Look. Look, look,
look, look, look.

04:06.880 --> 04:08.981
Look, see?

04:08.983 --> 04:11.984
See? See the symbols?
The symbols?

04:11.986 --> 04:13.685
They don't think
i know what it means,

04:13.687 --> 04:17.422
but I do! I do!
I understand what it means.

04:19.392 --> 04:21.860
Cami, this is a flyer
for a Chinese restaurant.

04:23.997 --> 04:27.966
No! You are no--
you are not my sister.

04:27.968 --> 04:29.868
They sent you.
They sent you.

04:29.870 --> 04:31.370
They sent you to trick me!

04:31.372 --> 04:33.705
- Cami-- cami--
- I am not forsaken!

04:33.707 --> 04:35.340
I'm the chosen one.

04:35.342 --> 04:37.476
I'm not forsaken.
I am the chosen one.

04:37.478 --> 04:39.478
I'm not forsaken.
I am the chosen one!

04:39.480 --> 04:41.380
Cami, are you off
your medication?

04:41.382 --> 04:41.380
Where are your pills?

04:41.382 --> 04:52.024
I am not forsaken,
i am the chosen one.
They cannot come against me.

04:58.765 --> 05:00.932
Cami, stop for a second.
Take your pills.

05:00.934 --> 05:03.468
Okay? Take the pills.
Just take the pill--

05:03.470 --> 05:05.737
ow!

05:05.739 --> 05:07.906
God.

05:18.751 --> 05:21.420
Uh, 27, I've got both the victim
and the suspect here.

05:24.958 --> 05:27.459
Are you the sister?
Autumn bergman?

05:27.461 --> 05:28.694
Step-sister.

05:28.696 --> 05:30.395
My name is Anne Matthews.

05:30.397 --> 05:31.563
I'm with the department
of mental health,

05:31.565 --> 05:32.964
L.A. county.

05:32.966 --> 05:35.567
I have a few questions
regarding your sister.

05:35.569 --> 05:37.602
Do you know how long
she's been off her meds?

05:37.604 --> 05:39.371
No, I don't.

05:39.373 --> 05:40.772
How long has she been
exhibiting this behavior?

05:40.774 --> 05:43.975
Um, ever since our--

05:43.977 --> 05:45.811
well, my father
and her mother died.

05:45.813 --> 05:48.547
- Uh-huh.
- They were in a car accident.

05:48.549 --> 05:49.948
It's gotten worse since then.

05:49.950 --> 05:51.516
Three years at least.

05:51.518 --> 05:52.951
May I just say that
in the past two months

05:52.953 --> 05:55.821
cops have been called out
six times on a 5150.

05:55.823 --> 05:58.457
Now, cami is smart enough
to know the system

05:58.459 --> 06:00.392
and that there's only
a 72-hour hold.

06:00.394 --> 06:01.927
So what can be done?

06:01.929 --> 06:04.463
Well, the cycle will continue
until she goes to jail

06:04.465 --> 06:05.797
or gets real treatment,

06:05.799 --> 06:08.033
which is what she needed
in the first place--

06:08.035 --> 06:10.402
a treatment facility.

06:10.404 --> 06:13.004
Now, her mom died.

06:13.006 --> 06:15.073
Is there any other
next of kin?

06:15.075 --> 06:17.409
I'm the only family she has.

06:17.411 --> 06:19.478
Well, you have
a big decision to make.

06:19.480 --> 06:21.546
Cami harmed
multiple people tonight.

06:21.548 --> 06:23.915
Herself as well
as officers included.

06:23.917 --> 06:28.120
There will be charges
brought against her.

06:28.122 --> 06:31.056
But, you know, see,
that's why I'm here.

06:31.058 --> 06:34.025
After she's booked,
i will work with her lawyer

06:34.027 --> 06:35.894
on a plea deal
for her to enter

06:35.896 --> 06:39.064
into a long-term treatment
program instead of jail time.

06:39.066 --> 06:41.133
No, cami would never
agree to that.

06:41.135 --> 06:43.668
That's not her decision.
It's yours.

06:43.670 --> 06:45.904
You being
the only next of kin,

06:45.906 --> 06:47.672
we can do
an emergency petition

06:47.674 --> 06:50.909
downtown tomorrow morning
for a conservatorship,

06:50.911 --> 06:54.045
and that means you would be
making the decisions for cami

06:54.047 --> 06:55.847
as long as the judge sees fit.

06:55.849 --> 06:57.749
I don't know.

06:57.751 --> 07:00.419
Look, I don't know if cami would
do well in a facility.

07:00.421 --> 07:01.987
She's not doing well out here.

07:01.989 --> 07:03.889
Autumn,
it's the only choice.

07:03.891 --> 07:07.025
Cami's gonna end up killing
herself or somebody else.

07:07.027 --> 07:08.160
She needs this.

07:08.162 --> 07:10.562
You're doing the right thing.

07:10.564 --> 07:12.631
I hope so.

07:12.633 --> 07:14.733
- I know.
- I understand.

07:14.735 --> 07:17.869
Autumn! Please. Sis, please.
Don't let them take me.

07:17.871 --> 07:20.005
It's okay. It's okay.
It's gonna be okay.

07:20.007 --> 07:21.173
You have to go.

07:24.545 --> 07:26.945
You have to go.

07:31.884 --> 07:34.219
Your books changed my life.

07:34.221 --> 07:36.488
When I broke my leg
and I couldn't leave the house,

07:36.490 --> 07:38.523
I read them all the way through
without stopping.

07:38.525 --> 07:40.692
-You helped me heal.
-That is so nice of you to say.

07:40.694 --> 07:41.927
Which one was your favorite?

07:41.929 --> 07:44.830
Your first one.
"Fields of silver."

07:44.832 --> 07:47.899
I cried so hard
i think I was dehydrated.

07:47.901 --> 07:49.501
Well, thank you for coming.

07:49.503 --> 07:51.069
Thanks.

07:53.473 --> 07:55.774
Well, hello. And who can
i make this out to?

07:55.776 --> 07:58.076
Jessie. "To Jessie,
don't stop writing,

07:58.078 --> 07:59.911
and don't give up
on your dream."

07:59.913 --> 08:02.481
- Are you a writer?
- Yes.

08:02.483 --> 08:03.982
I write
murder mystery stories,

08:03.984 --> 08:06.718
but my teacher says
I'm too young

08:06.720 --> 08:08.753
to be writing
about that kind of stuff,

08:08.755 --> 08:11.223
so I want you to write that
on the inside there

08:11.225 --> 08:12.858
so I can read it to myself

08:12.860 --> 08:15.660
when they all tell me
I'm too young.

08:21.000 --> 08:23.702
"Don't ever give up
on your dreams, Jessie,

08:23.704 --> 08:27.639
no matter who or what
tries to stop you."

08:27.641 --> 08:30.775
I won't. Thank you.

08:32.645 --> 08:33.979
This just came for you.

08:33.981 --> 08:36.515
- We need to wrap this up.
- Okay.

08:36.517 --> 08:39.116
One second please.

08:50.663 --> 08:52.564
Hey, babe.

08:52.566 --> 08:55.166
Oh. You were out
like a light.

08:55.168 --> 08:57.168
Yeah. Tired.

08:57.170 --> 09:00.171
Baby's been kicking me
all morning.

09:00.173 --> 09:01.606
You know,
i still can't believe

09:01.608 --> 09:03.642
that you binge-watch
these cop shows.

09:03.644 --> 09:05.944
Well, you know
that I like to see

09:05.946 --> 09:07.112
how they solve the murders.

09:07.114 --> 09:08.547
Yeah.

09:08.549 --> 09:09.548
Oh, my god.

09:09.550 --> 09:11.249
What is it?

09:11.251 --> 09:12.817
The 3-d imaging place,

09:12.819 --> 09:14.085
they just emailed me
the sonogram.

09:14.087 --> 09:16.955
Look.
That's our baby's face.

09:20.159 --> 09:22.060
That's our baby.

09:31.837 --> 09:37.008
My whole life,
I've waited for this moment.

09:37.010 --> 09:39.778
A child. I mean...

09:39.780 --> 09:43.915
I can't believe
I'm gonna be a father.

09:43.917 --> 09:47.152
Thank you.

09:48.321 --> 09:49.988
Thank you, des.
Thank you.

09:49.990 --> 09:52.657
I just--
i can't believe I doubted

09:52.659 --> 09:54.125
the fertility
treatments were working.

09:54.127 --> 09:55.827
It's...

10:00.166 --> 10:03.034
All the money in the world
isn't worth this moment.

10:09.075 --> 10:10.875
Two kilos were missing.

10:10.877 --> 10:12.344
If you don't tell us
what we need to know,

10:12.346 --> 10:15.246
we're gonna have child services
take your baby.

10:15.248 --> 10:17.882
You ain't taking my baby.

10:17.884 --> 10:19.784
I already told yo' ass

10:19.786 --> 10:21.319
I don't know nothing
about no drugs.

10:21.321 --> 10:24.356
Now you bring your ass back up
in my house here again

10:24.358 --> 10:26.891
and you ain't never
gonna leave.

10:26.893 --> 10:29.694
Not alive, at least.

10:29.696 --> 10:31.663
Carmen, that was great.

10:31.665 --> 10:34.766
Yeah, that, was,
uh, that was hot.

10:34.768 --> 10:37.335
Um, I wanna take
a different approach.

10:37.337 --> 10:38.837
I wanna try something
a little different.

10:38.839 --> 10:42.240
Like, um, play it
a little less tough.

10:42.242 --> 10:43.675
You know what I'm saying?

10:43.677 --> 10:45.276
Like she got
a lot more to lose.

10:45.278 --> 10:46.811
You understand
what I'm saying?

10:46.813 --> 10:50.048
I-- I think so.
Just give me one minute.

10:50.050 --> 10:52.217
Cool.

11:04.764 --> 11:08.700
Come on. We know you was there
the night Ricardo got shot.

11:08.702 --> 11:10.101
Two kilos went missing.

11:10.103 --> 11:11.770
If you don't tell us
what we need to know,

11:11.772 --> 11:13.938
we're gonna have child services
take your baby.

11:15.374 --> 11:19.077
You ain't taking my baby.

11:19.079 --> 11:20.945
Now, I already done
told yo' ass,

11:20.947 --> 11:23.982
I don't know nothing
about no drugs.

11:23.984 --> 11:27.085
No, you bring your ass
back up here in my house

11:27.087 --> 11:30.188
and you ain't
never gonna leave.

11:30.190 --> 11:32.123
'Least not alive.

11:34.427 --> 11:36.294
That was hot. Yeah.

11:36.296 --> 11:38.897
We loved you, by the way,
in "blazing hearts."

11:38.899 --> 11:40.765
Oh, thank you. Yeah, that was
one of my leading roles--

11:40.767 --> 11:42.133
my first leading role,

11:42.135 --> 11:43.802
and I was so excited
to work with everybody,

11:43.804 --> 11:45.303
especially
Michael Goldstein.

11:45.305 --> 11:47.072
He is an amazing director.

11:47.074 --> 11:48.773
Yeah, he is.

11:48.775 --> 11:50.141
- Yeah.
- Great.

11:50.143 --> 11:51.843
Well, have a wonderful day.

11:51.845 --> 11:54.345
Thank you.
Thank you so much.

11:59.218 --> 12:00.485
I did it two different ways,

12:00.487 --> 12:02.187
but I knew the first time
was right.

12:02.189 --> 12:04.723
They were just testing to see
if I can take direction.

12:04.725 --> 12:06.324
Yeah, well...

12:06.326 --> 12:08.960
All right, let me know
as soon as they give feedback.

12:10.096 --> 12:13.098
All right.

12:13.100 --> 12:14.899
Bye.

12:35.254 --> 12:37.288
And your ice cream.

12:37.290 --> 12:39.491
Mm, thank you, babe.

12:39.493 --> 12:41.326
Oh, this was
on the door for you.

12:41.328 --> 12:43.161
Oh. Okay.

12:43.163 --> 12:44.529
Okay, so you're good?
You have everything you need?

12:44.531 --> 12:46.131
If I need anything,
I'll call you.

12:46.133 --> 12:47.932
All right. I love you.

12:47.934 --> 12:49.334
I love you, too.

12:49.336 --> 12:51.336
-Have a good day at work, hon.
-All right.

13:08.888 --> 13:12.323
Guys, I just don't think
it's a very good idea.

13:12.325 --> 13:14.292
We put her away.

13:14.294 --> 13:15.960
If she wants to meet us all
to apologize,

13:15.962 --> 13:17.996
I think we can at least
give her a bit of our time.

13:17.998 --> 13:20.131
That girl is
holding nothing for me.

13:20.133 --> 13:23.234
You think it's part
of some sort of 12-step
program or something?

13:23.236 --> 13:25.403
- I don't know.
- Probably.

13:29.074 --> 13:31.543
"I have a lot to say to you
and apologize for.

13:31.545 --> 13:34.145
I need your help
in moving forward with my life.

13:34.147 --> 13:35.947
I have something
very important to tell you.

13:35.949 --> 13:37.115
Please."

13:37.117 --> 13:38.416
I don't trust it.

13:38.418 --> 13:39.584
Who knows
what she's been up to

13:39.586 --> 13:41.286
for the last two years?

13:41.288 --> 13:44.055
Very true. We really don't know
how stable she is.

13:44.057 --> 13:47.091
I would maybe meet with her
if I wasn't feeling like this.

13:47.093 --> 13:49.194
I get these waves of tiredness
where I can't even walk.

13:49.196 --> 13:51.863
That's 'cause you're hosting
a parasite in your body.

13:51.865 --> 13:53.565
I'm just kidding.

13:53.567 --> 13:56.100
Aw, I didn't mean it.
I didn't.

13:56.102 --> 13:58.036
No, seriously,
though, physically,

13:58.038 --> 14:00.572
I'm really-- I don't know,
I'm just not up to it.

14:00.574 --> 14:02.841
What could she
possibly have to say
that's so important?

14:02.843 --> 14:04.209
"Oh, I'm sorry for trying
to ruin your life

14:04.211 --> 14:06.110
or make your life
a living hell, or--"

14:06.112 --> 14:08.446
seriously? You two
are being so selfish.

14:08.448 --> 14:09.881
Do you know how much
guts it took

14:09.883 --> 14:12.183
for cami to even
write us these letters?

14:12.185 --> 14:13.618
Yes, she made our lives hell,

14:13.620 --> 14:16.554
but a lot can change.
A person can change.

14:16.556 --> 14:20.225
People don't change.
Circumstances do.

14:20.227 --> 14:22.393
What if you
were in her boat,

14:22.395 --> 14:24.429
trying to apologize
to your former best friends?

14:24.431 --> 14:26.097
Okay, she is not
your former best friend.

14:26.099 --> 14:27.632
She is your sister.
Let's not forget that.

14:27.634 --> 14:28.967
You have more willingness
to forgive her

14:28.969 --> 14:30.001
than Carmen and I.

14:30.003 --> 14:31.903
Autumn, don't you remember

14:31.905 --> 14:33.238
all the shit she pulled

14:33.240 --> 14:35.106
before we finally
could get her committed?

14:35.108 --> 14:37.008
Yes, of course I remember.

14:37.010 --> 14:38.509
But think about how I feel.

14:38.511 --> 14:41.112
Don't you think I hurt?

14:41.114 --> 14:43.147
She's the only family
that I have left.

14:46.986 --> 14:48.586
My dad would have wanted me

14:48.588 --> 14:50.455
to give her a second chance.
Can't you understand that?

14:54.059 --> 14:58.363
Okay, what if this
had happened to one of us?

14:58.365 --> 15:00.098
Carmen, what if you
were mentally ill?

15:00.100 --> 15:02.100
I damn near sometimes
think I am. Shit.

15:02.102 --> 15:03.434
I'm serious.

15:03.436 --> 15:05.003
You have your crazy moments

15:05.005 --> 15:06.471
when we think
you're out of your mind.

15:06.473 --> 15:09.340
Especially when it comes
to your career.

15:09.342 --> 15:12.677
And, des, I mean, this could
have easily been you.

15:12.679 --> 15:14.545
Look at you in college,

15:14.547 --> 15:16.347
how many times
you blacked out,

15:16.349 --> 15:17.515
woke up not knowing
where you were

15:17.517 --> 15:20.184
and who
you were lying next to.

15:20.186 --> 15:23.154
And that withdrawal you had
when you gave up drinking.

15:23.156 --> 15:26.991
Yes, but alcohol
and mixing schizophrenia
and crystal meth,

15:26.993 --> 15:28.626
Autumn,
it's two different things.

15:28.628 --> 15:31.162
You're missing the point.

15:31.164 --> 15:33.464
You had your chance
to turn your life around.

15:33.466 --> 15:35.967
Who are we to stand
in her way to do the same?

15:35.969 --> 15:39.570
Okay, fine. You win.

15:39.572 --> 15:41.339
Jesus.

15:41.341 --> 15:44.309
I can't deal with all these
emotions today.

15:44.311 --> 15:46.978
Autumn, we're doing this
for you, okay?

15:46.980 --> 15:50.048
We'll meet with cami,
let her say what she has to say,

15:50.050 --> 15:52.717
but that does not mean
that she's coming back
into our lives, okay?

15:52.719 --> 15:56.688
And we'll all do it together,
and that'll be that.

15:56.690 --> 15:59.724
Thank you, guys.

15:59.726 --> 16:03.161
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

16:03.163 --> 16:04.562
I need more of this wine.

16:04.564 --> 16:07.265
You ordered more carbs
than I've had all year.

16:07.267 --> 16:09.567
I'm feeding two, remember?
My parasite.

16:09.569 --> 16:12.270
Wait, so whose place
are we having this meeting at?

16:12.272 --> 16:13.471
Well, where's cami staying?

16:13.473 --> 16:16.541
You know cami.
She will surface.

16:16.543 --> 16:18.276
Autumn, I say
we do it at your house.

16:18.278 --> 16:21.079
Mm-mm. The last time cami
was at my house,

16:21.081 --> 16:23.314
she stole a faberge egg
and pawned it to buy drugs.

16:23.316 --> 16:24.716
Well, she stole
tom's diamond cufflinks

16:24.718 --> 16:26.751
and god knows what else.

16:26.753 --> 16:28.486
And my grandmother's
Ruby necklace
and blu-ray player.

16:28.488 --> 16:30.088
Okay, so our houses are out.

16:30.090 --> 16:32.256
Well, what about a restaurant
or a Starbucks?

16:32.258 --> 16:34.292
No, 'cause if
it's a public place
and she makes a scene,

16:34.294 --> 16:35.727
that would not be good
for my career.

16:35.729 --> 16:38.029
Okay. What about a park?

16:38.031 --> 16:40.031
There's not enough
people there.

16:40.033 --> 16:41.599
Motel room?

16:41.601 --> 16:45.470
Seems a little impersonal.

16:45.472 --> 16:48.272
What about we just rent
an apartment for the day?

16:48.274 --> 16:50.008
That's a really good idea.

16:50.010 --> 16:51.476
That way she can think
it's one of your houses

16:51.478 --> 16:53.077
and feel welcomed.

16:53.079 --> 16:55.013
Carmen, we can say
it's your new place.

16:55.015 --> 16:56.647
Okay, fine.

16:56.649 --> 16:58.549
Once you hear from her,
I'll book it online.

16:58.551 --> 17:00.084
Then we have
our little pow-wow,

17:00.086 --> 17:03.021
go our merry way,
and have a clean slate.

17:03.023 --> 17:04.321
See? It all worked out.

17:04.324 --> 17:06.089
Everything is gonna be fine.

17:11.130 --> 17:13.498
Anyway, thanks for helping me
set this place up.

17:13.500 --> 17:15.532
These gifts, I mean,
i just wanna get it all done

17:15.535 --> 17:16.733
before he gets back from...

17:16.736 --> 17:18.502
Oh, honey,
i charge 50 an hour.

17:18.505 --> 17:20.104
Cash only. Thank you.

17:20.106 --> 17:22.272
Okay. I get it now.

17:25.744 --> 17:29.347
- Come here quick.
- What?

17:29.349 --> 17:31.349
Quick. Quick.

17:33.352 --> 17:35.586
It's the first time
he's kicking.

17:35.588 --> 17:37.722
Wow.

17:37.724 --> 17:39.724
Wow. Ooh, wow.

17:42.161 --> 17:44.662
He kicked me.
Does it hurt?

17:44.664 --> 17:46.631
No. No, it doesn't.

17:46.633 --> 17:48.299
Who would have thought

17:48.301 --> 17:50.368
that two nine-year-old
little girls from Van nuys

17:50.370 --> 17:52.670
would be sitting
in a Beverly hills mansion,

17:52.672 --> 17:54.439
sipping iced tea
out of crystal glasses

17:54.441 --> 17:56.407
and discussing
diamond necklaces?

17:56.409 --> 17:58.076
I know.

17:58.078 --> 17:59.377
Well, we did it together.

17:59.379 --> 18:01.145
Yeah.

18:01.147 --> 18:02.847
You know, I wonder what
our lives would have been like

18:02.849 --> 18:05.416
if we never would have
met at girl scouts

18:05.418 --> 18:07.785
or never
would have met Autumn.

18:07.787 --> 18:11.656
Very different. I mean,
no weekend trips to Malibu

18:11.658 --> 18:13.191
with her family.

18:13.193 --> 18:15.293
No New York
high school celebration

18:15.295 --> 18:16.527
for graduation with her dad

18:16.529 --> 18:18.129
when he did
his book signing there.

18:18.131 --> 18:19.530
And you definitely
would have got kicked out

18:19.532 --> 18:21.199
freshman year from ucla

18:21.201 --> 18:23.134
if her dad didn't know
the department head.

18:23.136 --> 18:24.502
And you wouldn't have gotten
into the actor's studio

18:24.504 --> 18:25.870
if he didn't
make that phone call.

18:25.872 --> 18:28.239
Oh, yes, I would have,
thank you very much.

18:28.241 --> 18:30.608
Well, either way,
we owe Autumn and her dad

18:30.610 --> 18:31.809
for a lot of the good things

18:31.811 --> 18:32.810
that have happened
in our lives.

18:32.812 --> 18:34.278
Yeah, we do.

18:35.848 --> 18:38.716
- I'm afraid for her.
- Because of the dinner?

18:38.718 --> 18:40.518
Yeah.

18:40.520 --> 18:41.853
She's not as strong as us,
Carmen,

18:41.855 --> 18:43.454
and she doesn't--
she wasn't born

18:43.456 --> 18:45.123
with that fire inside of her.

18:45.125 --> 18:47.358
And if cami
really hasn't changed,

18:47.360 --> 18:49.227
I'm just afraid
that she's gonna go

18:49.229 --> 18:50.428
into this deep
depression again,

18:50.430 --> 18:51.596
just like the last time.

18:51.598 --> 18:52.730
That's what we're here for.

18:52.732 --> 18:54.265
And I can really care less

18:54.267 --> 18:55.733
what that thief cami
has to say to me.

18:55.735 --> 18:57.335
You cross me once...

18:57.337 --> 18:58.870
Then you better not
come across me again.

18:58.872 --> 19:00.805
Yeah, I know. I know.

19:00.807 --> 19:03.574
I just think of her dad,
and...

19:03.576 --> 19:04.709
If he would have seen what--

19:04.711 --> 19:06.777
we're doing it for him.

19:08.847 --> 19:10.381
Yeah, you're right.

19:11.918 --> 19:13.484
Pizza's ready.

19:13.486 --> 19:15.653
Oh. Come on, mama.

19:15.655 --> 19:17.455
- Ugh.
- Big belly.

19:29.902 --> 19:31.435
Hello.

19:31.437 --> 19:32.904
Hey, cami texted me.

19:32.906 --> 19:34.438
She wants to meet
Friday at 7:00.

19:34.440 --> 19:35.540
Does that work for you?

19:35.542 --> 19:37.208
It's good for me and des.

19:37.210 --> 19:39.510
- That's fine.
- Have you found a place?

19:39.512 --> 19:41.179
I did.

19:41.181 --> 19:42.880
Perfect. Thanks, Carmen.

19:42.882 --> 19:44.549
I know this isn't easy.

19:44.551 --> 19:46.450
Anything for you guys.

19:46.452 --> 19:48.786
- See you Friday.
- Bye.

20:01.767 --> 20:04.669
Jacob? Hi.

20:04.671 --> 20:06.370
Uh, Carmen.

20:06.372 --> 20:07.905
Right.

20:07.907 --> 20:10.408
I'm so sorry.
I'm running behind.

20:10.410 --> 20:11.876
I wanted to do
a quick maintenance check

20:11.878 --> 20:13.844
of everything in the house,
and everything is fine.

20:13.846 --> 20:17.481
I just wanted to just finish up
this smoke detector.

20:17.483 --> 20:20.685
Why don't you, uh, take a look
around the house

20:20.687 --> 20:23.988
and I'll come out there
and give you the lay
of the land?

20:41.440 --> 20:44.408
So I just wanna give you
my cell number

20:44.410 --> 20:46.344
since my home number
is on the agreement.

20:46.346 --> 20:50.615
So if you need me for anything,
you can get me at any time.

20:50.617 --> 20:52.483
And I don't want
to make you feel awkward,

20:52.485 --> 20:56.420
but, um, I recognized you
on your rental profile picture.

20:56.422 --> 20:58.456
You're that actress,
the one who was in, um--

20:58.458 --> 21:00.458
- in "blazing hearts."
- Yes! Yes.

21:00.460 --> 21:02.927
That's the one.
You were so good.

21:02.929 --> 21:04.562
Thank you.

21:04.564 --> 21:06.364
I'm a huge fan.

21:06.366 --> 21:08.833
Oh, that's sweet.

21:08.835 --> 21:12.403
I'm gonna watch
everything you're in.

21:12.405 --> 21:15.006
All right,
it was nice meeting you.

21:15.008 --> 21:16.974
Have fun with your friends.

21:19.745 --> 21:21.912
Thanks.

21:29.621 --> 21:34.592
That's about right. Mm.

21:38.998 --> 21:40.865
Who is it?

21:40.867 --> 21:42.533
It's your favorite person
in the world.

21:42.535 --> 21:43.534
Oprah?

21:46.005 --> 21:47.938
Nice place.

21:47.940 --> 21:49.940
Good job finding it.

21:49.942 --> 21:52.510
Thanks.

21:52.512 --> 21:54.378
Whew.
How are you feeling?

21:54.380 --> 21:55.946
I'm good, you know.

21:55.948 --> 21:57.915
Having a watermelon
strapped to your stomach

21:57.917 --> 21:59.884
- 24/7 can get old real quick.
- Uh-uh.

21:59.886 --> 22:01.686
Especially when you
got a bad back like I do.

22:01.688 --> 22:03.888
I know. That's why
I'm never having kids.

22:03.890 --> 22:06.557
I'll adopt, but ain't nothing
ever popping out of me.

22:06.559 --> 22:10.728
Oh, you say that now,
but you might change your mind.

22:10.730 --> 22:12.430
You cooked, Carmen.

22:12.432 --> 22:14.532
Yeah, I made cami's favorite,
Italian.

22:14.534 --> 22:16.734
Who knows the last time
she had a home-cooked meal.

22:16.736 --> 22:18.969
That was nice of you.

22:18.971 --> 22:21.072
And I see you brought
some wine, too.

22:21.074 --> 22:24.709
I need this to loosen up.
This is hard for me.

22:24.711 --> 22:26.644
Remember to breathe.

22:30.383 --> 22:32.083
- Nice place.
- Ooh, you scared me.

22:32.085 --> 22:34.418
Hey. You look great.

22:34.420 --> 22:35.853
Oh, thank you.

22:35.855 --> 22:37.655
- New shoes?
- Yeah, I got 'em on sale.

22:37.657 --> 22:38.989
- Nice.
- Right?

22:38.991 --> 22:40.358
Yeah.

22:40.360 --> 22:41.692
Jeez, what a great place,
Carmen.

22:41.694 --> 22:42.793
I'm glad you approve.

22:42.795 --> 22:44.061
- Drink of choice?
- Oh, thank you.

22:44.063 --> 22:46.097
Mm-hmm.

22:46.099 --> 22:47.365
Well, thanks again,
guys, for doing this.

22:47.367 --> 22:48.699
I really appreciate it.

22:48.701 --> 22:50.401
It's okay.

22:50.403 --> 22:51.969
Yeah, I just want her
to come and say her peace

22:51.971 --> 22:53.771
and be on her way.

22:53.773 --> 22:56.707
Well, I found
some great options online.

22:56.709 --> 23:00.044
Maybe we can all passively
suggest some of them to her.

23:00.046 --> 23:01.712
Group homes.
Support groups.

23:01.714 --> 23:03.614
Good idea.

23:03.616 --> 23:05.483
Well, that's if she's not
already living somewhere.

23:05.485 --> 23:08.052
True. But at least
it'll show her that I care.

23:08.054 --> 23:09.820
Well, she should
be here soon.

23:09.822 --> 23:11.655
I mean, 'cause this food's
getting cold.

23:11.657 --> 23:13.491
Aw, she loves pasta.

23:13.493 --> 23:15.493
Yeah, I know, and I even tried
those vegan meatballs.

23:15.495 --> 23:16.927
I mean, they're not
as bad as I thought.

23:16.929 --> 23:18.162
I mean, they look like barf,

23:18.164 --> 23:19.830
but they taste
like the real thing.

23:19.832 --> 23:21.832
See, and so much better for you
and the environment.

23:21.834 --> 23:23.734
Mm. Sorry, guys.
I need to start eating.

23:23.736 --> 23:25.603
If I don't eat every few hours,
i get light-headed.

23:25.605 --> 23:27.138
You were like that
before you got pregnant.

23:27.140 --> 23:29.874
- What's the difference now?
- Shut up, Carmen.

23:29.876 --> 23:31.509
Hey, at least I didn't eat

23:31.511 --> 23:32.943
a whole red velvet cake
to myself on my birthday.

23:32.945 --> 23:34.678
Okay, first of all,
that was a one-time thing,

23:34.680 --> 23:36.614
and that was the best
red velvet cake I have ever had.

23:36.616 --> 23:38.449
Yeah, and you were
the only one who would know

23:38.451 --> 23:40.484
since you ate the whole thing
before we could get a piece.

23:40.486 --> 23:42.553
Well, it's not my fault
you guys are always late.

23:42.555 --> 23:44.021
Well, we're here
on time today.

23:44.023 --> 23:47.491
Yeah, you knew better
than to be late today.

23:47.493 --> 23:48.926
What if she doesn't show up?

23:51.163 --> 23:53.597
I wouldn't do that
to you, sis.

23:55.000 --> 23:57.568
Cami.

23:57.570 --> 24:00.504
Wow, you look...

24:00.506 --> 24:02.072
Great.

24:02.074 --> 24:03.941
Thanks, sis.

24:05.710 --> 24:07.478
Cami.

24:07.480 --> 24:09.780
Carmen, I could smell
your cooking from down the hall.

24:11.850 --> 24:14.485
And, des,
you're pregnant.

24:14.487 --> 24:16.720
Yeah,
we finally got lucky.

24:16.722 --> 24:20.658
Luck has nothing
to do with it.

24:20.660 --> 24:23.494
So, cami, are you hungry?

24:23.496 --> 24:24.995
Starved.

24:24.997 --> 24:26.764
Autumn, why don't you
take her out to the back

24:26.766 --> 24:28.199
and wait for dinner?

24:28.201 --> 24:30.801
- Is this your new place?
- Yeah, I just moved in.

24:30.803 --> 24:33.037
Nice.

24:55.160 --> 24:57.695
Uh, so, how have
you been feeling, des?

24:57.697 --> 24:59.230
Mm. I'm feeling good.

24:59.232 --> 25:00.865
I'm a little tired, but...

25:00.867 --> 25:02.633
Can't do much of anything.

25:02.635 --> 25:04.702
Well, fortunately it's not
like you have to work,

25:04.704 --> 25:07.505
so you get to be lazy
and still live a great life.

25:07.507 --> 25:09.573
Lucky you.

25:12.677 --> 25:14.812
Well, I guess I'll say it.

25:14.814 --> 25:17.748
What the hell
happened to you, cami?

25:17.750 --> 25:19.783
I waited for you when you were
released from the facility,

25:19.785 --> 25:21.051
and you never showed up.

25:21.053 --> 25:23.153
Now, two years later,
here you are.

25:23.155 --> 25:25.623
No calls, no letters.

25:25.625 --> 25:28.125
Where have you been staying?

25:28.127 --> 25:30.060
With a friend.

25:30.062 --> 25:31.695
What have you been doing?

25:31.697 --> 25:34.265
Looking for a job,
an apartment--

25:34.267 --> 25:36.934
just doing
what normal people do.

25:36.936 --> 25:39.737
Well, if you need help finding
a place or any references--

25:39.739 --> 25:42.039
thanks, des,
i really appreciate that,

25:42.041 --> 25:43.941
but I don't wanna be
a burden on you guys.

25:43.943 --> 25:43.941
Oh, you're not a burden.

25:43.943 --> 25:47.144
We just wanna make sure you
have the support if you need it.

25:47.146 --> 25:49.013
That's really kind,
but I just wanna

25:49.015 --> 25:51.815
say my peace
and then be on the way.

25:54.085 --> 25:57.221
So how was the program?
Did it help?

25:57.223 --> 25:59.290
I got a fresh perspective
on everything.

25:59.292 --> 26:01.125
Believe me.

26:01.127 --> 26:02.593
Well, that's great.

26:02.595 --> 26:04.728
Then why did you leave?

26:04.730 --> 26:07.798
Well, that's why I'm here,
in a way.

26:07.800 --> 26:09.800
You obviously
all got my letters,

26:09.802 --> 26:12.603
and I have some things
I'd like to say to you three.

26:12.605 --> 26:15.806
I, in my own way,
appreciate and understand

26:15.808 --> 26:17.675
what you were doing
by having me committed.

26:17.677 --> 26:18.943
You cared about me enough

26:18.945 --> 26:20.711
to try to get
my schizophrenia treated

26:20.713 --> 26:22.846
and to get off the heroin.

26:22.848 --> 26:25.015
You know,
it took me almost a year

26:25.017 --> 26:26.350
to stop being angry
with you guys

26:26.352 --> 26:29.853
and really appreciate
what you did.

26:29.855 --> 26:32.656
You saved my life.

26:32.658 --> 26:34.758
And I was no prize.
I know that.

26:34.760 --> 26:37.161
I did things to all three of you
that were shameful.

26:37.163 --> 26:39.229
And if I could take them back,
i would, but I can't.

26:39.231 --> 26:40.898
All I could do is just sit here

26:40.900 --> 26:42.600
over this amazing
plate of spaghetti

26:42.602 --> 26:44.335
and just beg
for your forgiveness

26:44.337 --> 26:45.970
and hope that we could just
let the past die

26:45.972 --> 26:47.371
so that I could
really move forward

26:47.373 --> 26:49.206
and get a fresh start
with my life.

26:49.208 --> 26:51.241
So I sincerely apologize
for all the pain

26:51.243 --> 26:55.079
that I've caused.

26:55.081 --> 26:57.147
Well, I forgive you.

26:57.149 --> 27:00.017
I forgive you, too.

27:00.019 --> 27:01.652
I forgive you, cami.

27:05.023 --> 27:07.191
Group hug?

27:11.296 --> 27:12.763
Whew. Well.

27:12.765 --> 27:13.764
Okay.

27:13.766 --> 27:15.265
Oh, uh, Carmen,

27:15.267 --> 27:16.700
I've been
following your career

27:16.702 --> 27:17.901
since I've had
the extra time.

27:17.903 --> 27:19.036
Congrats on
"blazing hearts."

27:19.038 --> 27:20.638
It was a really
great movie.

27:20.640 --> 27:22.873
Oh, thank you.
I'm so glad you liked it.

27:22.875 --> 27:24.842
Yeah, it's really been
opening some doors for me.

27:24.844 --> 27:26.310
I'm auditioning for things

27:26.312 --> 27:28.178
I never would have
been considered for before.

27:28.180 --> 27:29.713
I mean, I auditioned
for the Denzel Washington

27:29.715 --> 27:31.148
movie the other day, so...

27:31.150 --> 27:33.384
Wow. That's amazing.

27:33.386 --> 27:35.019
How did you get the audition

27:35.021 --> 27:37.321
for "blazing hearts,"
by the way?

27:37.323 --> 27:38.355
Oh, it was through a friend.

27:38.357 --> 27:39.923
I was recommended for the role

27:39.925 --> 27:41.258
because it was so
character specific,

27:41.260 --> 27:42.993
and they really
wanted somebody

27:42.995 --> 27:45.095
that could, you know,
go there for the role, so...

27:45.097 --> 27:47.865
I bet you did.

27:47.867 --> 27:51.869
And, uh, des,
how far along are you?

27:51.871 --> 27:54.672
About six months?

27:54.674 --> 27:57.141
Yeah, six months
of eating as much

27:57.143 --> 28:00.110
as my mouth can chew.

28:00.112 --> 28:03.113
Well, I'm glad you're finally
able to have a baby.

28:07.285 --> 28:10.220
Um, so, cami,

28:10.222 --> 28:12.222
what are your ideas
for finding a job?

28:12.224 --> 28:14.792
Mm, not me, yet, sis.

28:14.794 --> 28:18.095
Tell me about your book.
What's it about?

28:18.097 --> 28:22.132
Um, well, it's, um,
a family drama

28:22.134 --> 28:24.001
about two siblings...

28:24.003 --> 28:25.469
Whose mother dies

28:25.471 --> 28:26.970
and leaves them searching
for the meaning of life?

28:26.972 --> 28:28.305
Yeah, I read it.

28:28.307 --> 28:29.707
You know,
there's some parallels

28:29.709 --> 28:31.775
between that story
and our family.

28:31.777 --> 28:33.410
But, I mean, who would know
besides me?

28:33.412 --> 28:36.280
Good read, though.
Very emotional.

28:36.282 --> 28:38.382
I'm glad you liked it.

28:39.851 --> 28:41.852
- Shit.
- Are you okay?

28:41.854 --> 28:43.721
- Yeah, I just need a minute.
- Is it a contraction?

28:43.723 --> 28:46.023
No. Baby's just kicking
my ribs really hard.

28:46.025 --> 28:47.458
Ooh. Okay.

28:47.460 --> 28:49.359
Uh, where's the bathroom?

28:49.361 --> 28:52.162
- First door on your left.
- Thanks.

28:57.869 --> 28:59.870
